{
  "stem": "22447.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was in the what they called the rat house, which was the town hall, which is the main building in the town.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Germans, nothing more they like than a band and a uniform.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Give  them a band and a uniform, and a ceremonial show, and you win them over.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had to go on duty at 6 o'clock in the morning. 'Reveille' was 6 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was bitterly cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was told, 6 o'clock, when the clock strikes six in the clock tower, the bugler will sound 'Reveille.' And as he does that, you hoist the Union Jack up on the flagpole.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But make sure the white cross, the narrow white cross goes nearer to the flag pole.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The narrow stripe on the-- the white narrow stripe on the flag goes nearest to the flagpole.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure enough, 6 o'clock, I was there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was some Germans going to work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had their lunch boxes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the clock struck 6 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The bugler sounds 'Reveille.' and I pulled up the flag.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as I pulled up the flag, it suddenly struck me, what would the Germans have said, what they're reaction would have been.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's bad enough having an enemy flag and an enemy soldier hoisting the flag on one of your prestigious building.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the soldier that done it was Jewish on top of it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I don't know what they would have thought.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And from there, Schleswig-Holstein, I come back to England.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No-- we wasn't-- I don't think, I don't think it applies to the entire army, but as far as I was, I was concerned, we was not demobilized.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We was released.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
